A teacher at Sheikh Abdhalla Al Farsy Girls Secondary School in Mvita is on the spot for allegedly assaulting a student. A 17-year-old Form IV student is said to have been assaulted by her Biology teacher, injuring her face. The girl’s father says she was punished for noisemaking. “The watch the girl was wearing dropped and the teacher threw it on her face,” he said. But the teacher said the student slapped her. A doctor who treated the girl confirmed there was assault. Coast Kuppet official Linet Kamadi accused the parent of intimidating the school.